The paper proposes a deep neural framework for generating thumbnails of digital images, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as object detection and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of adaptive convolutions, which is a machine learning (ML) technique, indicating that it could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning (DL) techniques such as neural networks, which could place it in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
